				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="95th: Man-to-Man Skirmish Combat in the Napoleonic Wars" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>What: Wargame/RPG rules for small fights in the Peninsula War from 1808 - 1814.&amp;#10;Scale: Man to man combat. 1 figure equals 1 man.&amp;#10;Your Role: Players can command from one small group to multiple groups as you rise in Rank.&amp;#10;Playability: Designed for solo, same side and head to head play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;95th can be played in a variety of ways:&amp;#10;You can play as a member of a small band of soldiers.&amp;#10;You can play as the Leader of a small band of soldiers.&amp;#10;You can play larger games with multiple bands of soldiers.&amp;#10;The bottom line is you can play it any way you like, with any figures or counters you like.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Inside you&amp;rsquo;ll find:&amp;#10;60 full color card stock counters to get you into the game ASAP.&amp;#10;Rules for skirmish combat built around the famous British 95th Rifles&amp;#10;Four Armies to choose from - British, French, Portuguese and Spanish as well as Lists for Deserters, Guerrillas and the Civilian population&amp;#10;Nineteen different infantry and cavalry units to play as.&amp;#10;Fourteen different Missions for you to play.&amp;#10;A system that rewards your men when successful and punishes them when they fail; rising in Rank as you play.&amp;#10;Different Attributes that help make your Characters unique.&amp;#10;A minimal bookkeeping Campaign System that gives meaning to every game as the results of one will affect the outcome of the next.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
